The African Mining Indaba will kick off on Monday,  May 9th. It’s a gathering of mining industry players across the mining value chain from all over the world, as well as African government leaders, among others. Proceedings will formally start with the opening address by the Minister of Mineral Resources and Energy, Gwede Mantashe. South Africa is set to participate at the 2022 Investing in Africa Mining Indaba to be convened under the theme “Evolution of African Mining: Investing in the Energy Transition, ESG and the Economies”. Get all the updates & follow the discussions #InvestinSAMining #BelieveInSA?? pic.twitter.com/EPoJULsuBO — @Brand_SA (@Brand_SA) May 6, 2022  This year’s overarching theme is entitled Evolution of African Mining: Investing in the Energy Transition, ESG and the Economies. Sustainability is one of the key buzzwords, with the industry seeking to make progress and add to economic prosperity, while working to mitigate climate change.  